OL,3,C'The chippy should be a treat, but
OL,4,Cpeople need to be able to afford it'
OL,6,FHe wants help with energy bills so
OL,7,Ffamilies have more money left to spend
OL,8,Fon the high street, as costs are
OL,9,Frising and the price of some basic
OL,10,Fingredients has gone up by more than
OL,11,F50 per cent.
OL,13,FMr Stapleton said: "The cost of
OL,14,Fingredients has gone through the roof.
OL,16,F"Fish has gone from #65 or #70 to #100
OL,17,Fa box so that is quite the jump, and
OL,18,Fwe are trying to keep our costs down
OL,19,Ffor our customers so we are taking a
OL,20,Fbit of a hit ourselves."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
