OL,3,C'The chippy should be a treat, but
OL,4,Cpeople need to be able to afford it'
OL,6,FAnother said: "There's a lot more they
OL,7,Fcould be doing to help our own people.
OL,8,FSo they could be doing more to help
OL,9,Ffamilies with children, with childcare
OL,10,F- doing more with mental health."
OL,12,FAway from the town centre, a sixth-
OL,13,Fgeneration farmer described the budget
OL,14,Fas a make or break moment and wants
OL,15,Faction from ministers.
OL,17,FAndy Shaw says he cannot get a fair
OL,18,Fprice for the shed he has packed with
OL,19,Fpotatoes and argues the farm's costs
OL,20,Fhave spiralled beyond its profits.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
